<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 26 at 5:34AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>At 526 am, radar indicated a band of heavy snow extending from
southwest Cascade County through central Chouteau County, moving
east at 10 mph. Snowfall rates exceeding one inch per hour are
likely within this band of snow. One to three inches of snow have
fallen on I-15 from around Wolf Creek to Great Falls, and along
Highway 87 from Great Falls to Big Sandy. Consider delaying travel
along these sections of highway until conditions improve after
sunrise. Carry a winter safety kit if you travel, as temperatures
are below zero and dropping today.</description>
